## Multimedia Accessibility
[Captions, Transcripts, and Audio Descriptions - WebAIM](http://webaim.org/techniques/captions/)  
An overview of the use of captions, transcripts, and audio descriptions in accessible multimedia.
[Captioning Service Vendors - DCMP](https://www.dcmp.org/ai/10/)  
A list of vendors offering captioning services. The list is maintained by the federally-funded [Described and Captioned Media Program](https://dcmp.org/).
[Description Service Vendors - DCMP](https://dcmp.org/ai/179/)  
A list of vendors offering captioning services. The list is maintained by the federally-funded [Described and Captioned Media Program](https://dcmp.org/).
[Commercial Services For Producing Audio Description](http://www.acb.org/adp/services.html)  
The [American Council of the Blind](http://www.acb.org/)'s list of individual, organization, and corporate services that are involved with audio description. The commercial companies typically employ professional audio description personnel who write the description for movies, DVDs, and other media, while the organizations tend to provide audio description services via trained describers for local events.
